ADCB Heads to Highest Close Since 2008 on RHB Stake Sale Report

-- B y   A l a a   S h a h i n e
-- 
2011-06-16T09:51:52Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-16/adcb-heads-to-highest-close-since-2008-on-rhb-stake-sale-report.html
Abu Dhabi Commercial Bank PJSC (ADCB) 
headed for the highest close in more than two years after
Malaysian newspaper Star reported the lender is selling its 25
percent stake in RHB Capital Bhd. at 2.25 times book value.  The shares gained 2.5 percent to 3.24 dirhams at 1:40 p.m.
in the emirate, the highest level since October 2008. The
benchmark  ADX General Index (ADSMI)  advanced 0.6 percent.  The Abu Dhabi-based lender known as ADCB is selling its
stake to Aabar Investments PJSC at 10.80 ringgit a share, Star
reported, citing an unidentified person. An agreement on the
stake sale will be signed tomorrow, the newspaper said.  An ADCB spokesman, who didnâ€™t want to be identified in line
with company policy, declined to comment when contacted by
